20.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Blessings of Apollo</span><hr size=1> In a flash of blinding light appears the great Apollo. Around him are assembled the Muses, singing songs of marriage. He nods to the Amazon with a smile upon his angelic face<br>
<br>
&quot;It joys me to be able to bless you as such on this day. Marriage is but a thing not to be taken lightly. I wish you nothing but luck on your wedding day.&quot;<br>
<br>
He shakes the golden hair from his blue eyes and smiles.<br>
<br>
&quot;One musn't bless a wedding without bearing gifts! And I come with the most blessed gifts of all. I come with the blessing of Divine Inspiration, of Truth, and of Light.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Muses bow to the Amazon, outstretching there hands with gifts from Apollo, girdles of gold, and bows of silver. They soon though begin to dance and sing of the future and the prosperous marriage of the Amazon. Apollo smiles and takes his seat.<br>
<br>
