<br>
&quot;It seems Olympus has lost it's mind.  Since when in all of eternity have we gods and goddesses blessed an unbeliever?  Especially one who so boldly approaches Olympus?&quot;  His eyes turn now to the mortal and a dangerous lightning flashes in his eyes.  &quot;I would suggest you leave Olympus and return to your false prophet.  The one who has forsaken his own destiny and chosen to join himself with a mortal woman.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/16/01 9:09:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blessing an Unbeliever??</span><hr size=1> ::Poseidon addresses his brother Zeus in winged words::<br>
<br>
&quot;Dear brother calm your nerves. We as Olympians may bestow blessings on whom we will. Especially me. Would you question my actions? Question me for blessing this girl?&quot;<br>
<br>
::Poseidon looks around to the other Olympians and addresses them::<br>
<br>
&quot;Surely you must know it is a right of yours, you who are the gods and goddesses that live on high pillared Olympus. Even though Zeus be king, are all his ways just and right? They cannot be in everyone's eyes.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/17/01 12:13:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Unbeliever?</span><hr size=1> Alysia folded her arms as a golden aura wrapped around her. She smirked at Zeus while looking to Artemis and Athena.<br>
<br>
&quot;Unbeliever you say? Well who said that I was an Elisian? I only am marrying one Zeus.&quot;<br>
<br>
She then took a few steps around the area in which the other Gods stood.<br>
<br>
&quot;And I am welcome here as much as any of the other Gods and Goddesses. For I hold the title of such.&quot;<br>
<br>
So narrowed her eyes slightly.<br>
<br>
&quot;I do not put my worship in the Gods, more so my respect. But so far that is slowly falling.&quot;<br>
